---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'About Me';
const description = 'Learn more about my professional journey, academic pursuits, and expertise.';
const permalink = `${Astro.site.href}about`;
const baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} permalink={permalink} current="about">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="intro-text">
      Hello — I’m a software engineer and technology consultant. I spend most of my time somewhere between systems, data, and business problems that refuse to stay simple.
    </p>

    <p>
      I work on building and improving enterprise systems — from backend workflows and integrations to automation and operational tooling. If it involves making a messy process slightly less messy, I’m probably interested.
    </p>

    <h2>What I Actually Do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>IT Consulting:</strong> Helping teams figure out what’s broken, what’s outdated, and what needs to be rebuilt (or left alone if it still works).</li>
      <li><strong>Enterprise Systems & Integrations:</strong> Connecting tools, data, and processes so businesses don’t feel like ten different systems pretending to be one.</li>
      <li><strong>Automation:</strong> Removing repetitive work so humans can focus on things that don’t feel like copy-paste therapy.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Academic Side Quest</h2>
    <p>
      I’m currently pursuing an MSc alongside work. It’s a mix of theory, systems thinking, and trying to stay awake after consulting workdays.
    </p>

    <p>
      The interesting part is how often the two worlds overlap — what I learn in class tends to show up in real systems sooner than expected.
    </p>

    <h2>This Journal</h2>
    <p>
      This site is basically my public scratchpad.
    </p>

    <p>
      I write about work, systems, learning, and the occasional “why did this break at 2am” moment. It’s part technical notes, part reflection, part trying to make sense of everything in between.
    </p>

    <h2>Outside of Work</h2>
    <p>
      I’m usually thinking about systems — even when I’m not supposed to be. Or pushing blog posts from the terminal because clicking “publish” feels like too many steps.
    </p>

    <p>
      If you’re into software engineering, consulting, automation, or building things that quietly keep systems alive — we’ll probably get along.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .intro-text {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .about-image {
    float: right;
    margin: -1em -4em 2em 2em;
    max-width: 300px;
  }

  .about-image img {
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 0.5em;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1020px) {
    .about-image {
      float: none;
      margin: 0 auto 2em;
      text-align: center;
    }
  }
</style>